The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, Oct. 29: The number of unemployed all over the world in the 15-24 age group has risen nearly 15 per cent over the past decade, while south Asia accounts for a 10 per cent increase, a new ILO report said. The latest report on unemployment said while the number of the young unemployed increased from 74 million to 85 million between 1995 and 2005, nearly 300 million youths, which was approximately 25 per cent of their total population, lived below $2-per-day-poverty line.

 Moscow, Oct. 29: With India seeking sustained supply of one million barrels per day (mbd) of crude oil from Russia, petroleum and natural gas minister Murli Deora will hold talks with Russian ministers and energy officials on the issue during his visit to the country beginning tomorrow. 

 Tokyo, Oct. 29: Japan, the US, Canada and the EU will take concerted action against China at the World Trade Organisation to press Beijing to crack down on illegally copied and pirated products. Washington is expected to bring the case to the global trade body as early as next week.

 New Delhi, Oct. 29: Apprehending a loss of over Rs 1,650 crore to the exchequer by sale of equity in fertiliser cooperative Iffco at the face value by the previous NDA regime, the government is probing if any irregularities were committed in it.

 New Delhi, Oct. 29: Sebi is working on a user-friendly online language called XBRL (Extensible Business Reporting Language), a dictionary of data definition that incorporates the mechanism for describing, naming and classifying items of business information.

 New Delhi, Oct. 29: With infrastructure crying for long-term funding and external commercial borrowing having a cap of $18 billion in a year, the finance ministry is toying with the idea of allowing currency-swap to allow foreign funding in rupee-denominated loans.

 New Delhi, Oct. 29: With an eye on volumes to arrest erosion in crucial market share, Hero Honda has decided to strengthen presence in the 100-cc segment where it will launch new bikes.




